      <div class="body">
        <p><span class="dropcap">B</span>efore a child holds a pencil, she holds a scoop. Before she counts, she pours. Before she names a feeling, she squeezes a ball of dough until her chest goes quiet again. Sensory Play is the toolkit for that prior learning: maple trays sized for the Flisat, dual-sided tracing inserts, scented therapy dough, sand trays for the morning meeting reset. No batteries. No instructions. Just texture, attention, and the long, generous space between them.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars">
        <div class="p"><span class="label">Sensory Integration</span><p>Texture, weight, smell, the body learning.</p></div>
        <div class="p"><span class="label">Fine Motor</span><p>Scoop, pinch, pour, trace, place.</p></div>
        <div class="p"><span class="label">Self-Regulation</span><p>The quiet tool that resets a morning.</p></div>
        <div class="p"><span class="label">OT &amp; SLP-Friendly</span><p>Eligible under IDEA Part B &amp; Medicaid OT funding.</p></div>
